    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Alert on stock levels with HTTP / REST API and Gmail without manual work\n\n**Pattern:** Threshold Monitoring · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAlert on stock levels with HTTP / REST API and Gmail without manual work. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual portfolio tracking is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nEvery Few Minutes → Probe Endpoint A → Combine Probe Results → All Healthy? → Record Uptime Metric → Load Previous Snapshot → Compute Drift vs Snapshot → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to threshold monitoring without manual effort\n- Anyone automating portfolio tracking in finance\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Improves response time\n- Responds in seconds\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "9206da8e-c2cc-9477-0742-25fc2b3022ba",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -290
      ],
      "id": "b55e3d0c-1b6c-ed83-debf-55a083cb7e19",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -290
      ],
      "id": "60cd0963-909e-6ac3-842e-701b2bdaaa2f",
      "name": "🧹 Data quality"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your portfolio tracking process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
